insights: Your enthusiasm for biology is inspiring! Consider joining a biology club or group on campus to further explore your interests and connect with like-minded peers.
Joining public speaking is a great step toward leadership development. Look for workshops or seminars on campus that focus on public speaking and leadership skills to complement your involvement.
Practice makes perfect with public speaking. Try starting small by presenting in front of friends or family, then gradually increase your audience size as you gain more confidence.

Keep an eye out for opportunities to participate in conferences or symposiums related to biology. Presenting your ideas in such forums can be an excellent way to sharpen both your public speaking and scientific communication skills.
